  "commentary": "With SPX at 6990 trading just below the massive 7000 gamma wall (16.8B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push above this level while providing support on dips given the positive gamma regime. The -0.8% five-minute decline suggests dealers are already stepping in as buyers after the move away from 7000, with strong stabilizing forces from the 6975 level (5.4B GEX) providing a near-term floor. Watch for resistance at the 7000-7025-7050 gamma wall cluster and support at 6975, with price likely to remain range-bound between these levels.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to bounce back toward 7000 and trade sideways between 6975-7025.",
